            <thetext>Sieve is just taking the message file verbatim and sending it to sendmail to do
redirects.  It should probably make some effort to strip the Return-path header,
which is allowed to be sent, but is in violation of a SHOULD NOT.

The return-path header is in the file as an optimization for the common case
(delivery), and I suspect it should be easy to strip.

Applicable code is in lmtpd.c:send_forward()</thetext>
